<persona name="Eric" type="Primary" assumption_persona="FALSE" image="eric.jpg">
  <activities>Eric is Helen's 5 year old son.  Although not a webinos user as such, he does use sometimes use his mother's webinos-enabled tablet device when going on journeys.  Although Helen usually thinks about what Eric might do for long journeys, he is usually left to his own devices on short-duration trips like school-runs or shopping trips.</activities>
  <attitudes>Eric enjoys activities which draw the attention of others, and likes to involve other people in the games that he plays.  For this reason, Eric is particularly fond of playing simple games with his parents, such as I Spy.</attitudes>
  <aptitudes>As Eric has grown older, he has also developed an interest in activities which absorb his interest.  Card and memory games have been known to keep Eric distracted on long journeys.  Similarly, Eric is happy to watch films and take a snooze when feels a little tired.</aptitudes>
  <motivations>Eric focuses his energies on whatever technology he has to hand, but always looks for instant gratification based on his current needs.  Although he finds tables and touch-screens intriguing, he is prone to throwing down objects he doesn't like.  Eric will tolerate things he doesn't find immediately useful only if he expects a reward as a consequence of using it.
If Eric is going on long journeys, he takes comfort in his things which are familiar to him.  For example, Helen often gives Eric his teddy bear when travelling long distances, such as to a theme park or trips to his grandparents, and is usually unable to sleep on car journeys without this.  Although Eric doesn't hold his teddy bear all the time, he becomes distressed if unable to reach for this at any time from his seat.</motivations>
